                                "stop": 10.852,
                                "byte_start": 89578,
                                "byte_stop": 133046,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 00-201, New York Times Company versus Tasini, will be announced by Justice Ginsburg."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.852,
                        "stop": 337.867,
                        "byte_start": 133046,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.852,
                                "stop": 23.856,
                                "byte_start": 133046,
                                "byte_stop": 185082,
                                "text": "This case concerns the rights accorded freelance authors and a privilege accorded their publishers under Seciton 201(c) of the Copyright Act of 1976."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.856,
                                "stop": 36.812,
                                "byte_start": 185082,
                                "byte_stop": 236909,
                                "text": "The plaintiff\u2019s six freelancers contributed articles to three print publications, two newspapers, the New York Times and Newsday and one magazine, Sports Illustrated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.812,
                                "stop": 48.112,
                                "byte_start": 236909,
                                "byte_stop": 282048,
                                "text": "Without the author\u2019s permission, the print publishers authorized LEXIS\/NEXIS to place the author\u2019s articles into the Nexis database."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.112,
                                "stop": 60.198,
                                "byte_start": 282048,
                                "byte_stop": 330427,
                                "text": "The Times also authorized University Microfilms International to place Times articles into the New York Times OnDisc and General Periodicals OnDisc."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.198,
                                "stop": 71.79,
                                "byte_start": 330427,
                                "byte_stop": 376820,
                                "text": "The three databases have several common features, each contains articles from sequential editions of periodicals spanning many years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.79,
                                "stop": 78.95,
                                "byte_start": 376820,
                                "byte_stop": 405451,
                                "text": "In each, the user may search for articles based on criteria such as author, subject or headline."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.95,
                                "stop": 92.276,
                                "byte_start": 405451,
                                "byte_stop": 458740,
                                "text": "The user may view, print or download each article yielded by the search, each story appears to the user separately clear of the context provided by other items originally published in the same edition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.276,
                                "stop": 109.829,
                                "byte_start": 458740,
                                "byte_stop": 528958,
                                "text": "The freelance authors complained that their copyrights in their individual works were infringed when the defendant Electronic Publishers as licensed by the defendant Print Publishers, distributed the author\u2019s articles to the databases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.829,
                                "stop": 121.004,
                                "byte_start": 528958,
                                "byte_stop": 573679,
                                "text": "In response the publishers asserted that their actions were shielded by Section 201(c) of the Copyright Act, the meaning of that provision is \u201ckey to this case\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.004,
                                "stop": 140.132,
                                "byte_start": 573679,
                                "byte_stop": 650166,
                                "text": "The Section leaves author and publishers free to negotiate whatever arrangement they will, in default of private ordering, Section 201(c) declares that the freelancer retains, the copyrights in her contribution to a collective work like a magazine or newspaper."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.132,
                                "stop": 158.391,
                                "byte_start": 650166,
                                "byte_stop": 723204,
                                "text": "The publisher in the words of the statute is presumed to have acquired only the privilege of reproducing and distributing the contribution, as part of that particular collected work, any revision of that collective work, and a later collective work in the same series."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.391,
                                "stop": 163.661,
                                "byte_start": 723204,
                                "byte_stop": 744311,
                                "text": "The US District Court for the Southern District of New York, granted summary judgment for the publishers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.661,
                                "stop": 176.806,
                                "byte_start": 744311,
                                "byte_stop": 796869,
                                "text": "In that court\u2019s view, the databases copied to freelancers articles as part of a revision of the original periodical edition and so qualified for the Section 201(c) privilege."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.806,
                                "stop": 182.526,
                                "byte_start": 796869,
                                "byte_stop": 819753,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit reversed ordering entry of judgment for the authors."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.526,
                                "stop": 195.611,
                                "byte_start": 819753,
                                "byte_stop": 872102,
                                "text": "In the Court of Appeals\u0027 view, massive databases loaded with multitudes of individually retrievable articles are not revisions of particular newspaper or magazine editions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.611,
                                "stop": 203.337,
                                "byte_start": 872102,
                                "byte_stop": 902927,
                                "text": "But we hold that the Court of Appeals correctly construed Section 201(c) and we therefore affirmed its judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.337,
                                "stop": 211.966,
                                "byte_start": 902927,
                                "byte_stop": 937513,
                                "text": "The 1976 Copyright Act, aimed to improve the situation of freelance authors vis-\u00e0-vis their publishers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.966,
                                "stop": 229.478,
                                "byte_start": 937513,
                                "byte_stop": 1007521,
                                "text": "To that end Section 201(c) assures that if there is a demand for a freelance article, either standing alone or when a new collection, the freelancer can benefit from that demand after authorizing initial publication, the freelancer can sell the article to others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.478,
                                "stop": 241.941,
                                "byte_start": 1007521,
                                "byte_stop": 1057362,
                                "text": "The crucial statutory term of Section 201(c), relevant here, allows the publisher to reprint the article as part of a revision of the original collective work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.941,
                                "stop": 253.121,
                                "byte_start": 1057362,
                                "byte_stop": 1102084,
                                "text": "Like the Second Circuit, we cannot see how the databases perceptively copy articles as part of a revision of a particular edition of a newspaper or magazine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.121,
                                "stop": 259.382,
                                "byte_start": 1102084,
                                "byte_stop": 1127162,
                                "text": "One might view the articles as part of a new compendium, the entirety of works in the database."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.382,
                                "stop": 272.609,
                                "byte_start": 1127162,
                                "byte_stop": 1180034,
                                "text": "But the massive Database no more constitutes a \u0022revision\u0022 of each constituent edition than a 400-page novel quoting a solid in passing would constitute \u0022revision\u0022 of that poem."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 272.609,
                                "stop": 282.861,
                                "byte_start": 1180034,
                                "byte_stop": 1221098,
                                "text": "Alternatively, one could view the articles in the databases as part of no larger work at all, but simply as individual articles presented individually."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.861,
                                "stop": 290.279,
                                "byte_start": 1221098,
                                "byte_stop": 1250773,
                                "text": "But 201(c) does not authorize the publisher to copy individual articles discretely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 290.279,
                                "stop": 295.955,
                                "byte_start": 1250773,
                                "byte_stop": 1273447,
                                "text": "The publisher\u2019s privilege is in the collective work only, the edition as a whole."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 295.955,
                                "stop": 311.084,
                                "byte_start": 1273447,
                                "byte_stop": 1333947,
                                "text": "The publishers have warned that a ruling for the authors will decimate the electronic record of history, but today\u2019s decision means only that the publishers have infringed the author\u0027s copyrights and must provide appropriate regrets."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 311.084,
                                "stop": 319.572,
                                "byte_start": 1333947,
                                "byte_stop": 1367906,
                                "text": "The opinion does not necessitate a court order barring inclusion of the freelancer\u2019s articles in the databases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.572,
                                "stop": 332.132,
                                "byte_start": 1367906,
                                "byte_stop": 1418166,
                                "text": "Speculation about the publisher\u2019s response to our ruling moreover, provides no cause for this Court to shrink rights, Congress safeguarded to authors under Section 201(c)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 332.132,
                                "stop": 337.867,
                                "byte_start": 1418166,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion, in which Justice Breyer Joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
